description.plain: Black Belt Eagle Scout’s debut album, Mother of My Children begins with lead single “Soft Stud,” which Katherine Paul describes as her “queer anthem.” It’s “about the hardships of queer desire within an open relationship, which I think a lot of the queer community can relate to.”
